cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.MM 

This paper is primarily focused on computer vision algorithms for identifying interest points and establishing correspondences between them. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also introduces an unsupervised training methodology for interest point detectors, which involves predicting the probability of a given pixel being an inlier. This aspect of the paper could potentially fall under sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper evaluates the performance of the proposed detector on various datasets, which could fall under sub-categories such as cs.RO (Robotics) and cs.MM (Multimedia).
